This error occurs because TensorFlow attempts to load its own bundled version of OMP, conflicting with the system's `libiomp5.so`. The workaround involves navigating to your virtual environment's directory (`cd tf_skimage_venv`) and then executing a series of commands to patch the TensorFlow library installation to use the system-wide `libiomp5.so`:
```bash
export LIBIOMP_PATH=$(strace python -c 'from skimage.transform import AffineTransform' 2>&1 | grep -v ENOENT | grep -ohP -e '(?<=")[^"]+libiomp5.so(?=")' | xargs realpath)
find -path '*_solib_local*' -name libiomp5.so -exec ln -sf $LIBIOMP_PATH {} \;
```
